Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery closed vessel, probably an oinochoe; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of part of draped female figure (added white arm and hands; added red strokes and faded dots in groups of three on himation).
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B601.43)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0321) (Phase 1)
